The '''A368''' is a part [[primary status]] [[A roads in Great Britain|A road]] in [[North Somerset]], England. It runs from [[Marksbury]] (near [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]]) to [[Banwell]] (near [[Weston-super-Mare]]) along the northern edge of the [[Mendip Hills]] and past the reservoir at [[Chew Valley Lake]]. 
[[File:A368 at Chelwood - geograph.org.uk - 1206920.jpg|thumb|left|The A368 at Chelwood<BR>photographed March 2009]]
The road runs through the village of [[Chelwood]], where there is a roundabout for the junction with the [[A37 road|A37]], then via the village of [[Bishop Sutton]] to the large reservoir at Chew Valley Lake before crossing the B3114 at [[West Harptree]]. It then runs via [[Compton Martin]] to another smaller reservoir at [[Blagdon Lake]]. At [[Burrington, Somerset|Burrington]], there is a turning for the B3134 which leads through [[Burrington Combe]]. The road crosses the [[A38 road|A38]] at traffic lights just west of [[Churchill, Somerset|Churchill]], and goes through [[Sandford, Somerset|Sandford]] before ending at [[Banwell]] on the [[A371 road|A371]].

