[[File:Dyserth Waterfall.jpg|thumb|Dyserth waterfall]]
'''Dyserth Waterfall''' is a [[waterfall]] in [[Dyserth]], [[North Wales]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dyserth.com/waterfall.html |title=Dyserth - Waterfall |publisher=Dyserth.com |accessdate=2018-05-02}}</ref>
The [[river Ffyddion]], a [[tributary]] of the [[River Clwyd]], falls down a 70-foot ledge creating the waterfall. In the 1880s, [[mining]] in the area caused it to dry up, however when the mining stopped, the waterfall resumed its full flow.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.walesdirectory.co.uk/Towns_in_Wales/Dyserth_Town.htm |title=Dyserth tourist information |publisher=WalesDirectory.co.uk |accessdate=2018-05-02}}</ref>

