{{Infobox mountain | name = Emba Soira | other_name = '''እምባ ሶይራ''' | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 3018 | elevation_ref = <ref name="pb">[http://www.peakbagger.com/peak.aspx?pid=11114 "Soira, Eritrea" on Peakbagger.com] Retrieved 28 September 2011</ref> | prominence_m = | prominence_ref = | range = [[Eritrean Highlands]] | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | location = [[Debub Region]], [[Eritrea]] | map = Eritrea |relief=1 | range_coordinates = | map_caption = Eritrea | map_size = 250 | label_position = left | coordinates = {{coord|14|45|N|39|32|E|type:mountain_region:ER-DU_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | topo = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Emba Soira''' (also transliterated '''Sowera''') is the highest mountain in [[Eritrea]].<ref name="pb"/> Rising {{convert|3018|m|ft|0}} above sea level, it is part of the [[Eritrean Highlands]], one side of the [[Great Rift Valley, Ethiopia|Great Rift Valley]] which cuts through Eritrea and joins the [[Red Sea]]. The mountain is situated in the southeastern part of the [[Debub Region|Debub]] (Southern) administrative region in central Eritrea.
Emba Soira is reached by a paved road from the city of [[Senafe]], located 135 kilometres south of the national capital [[Asmara]]. From there, a very difficult and perilous dirt track heading east for almost 20 kilometres leads to the mountain. The last part must be trekked and takes at least a few hours of travel.
