{{distinguish|South Kara Depression}}
The '''Kara Depression''' is a [[depression (geology)|depression]] in the [[Extreme North]] of [[European Russia]], by the mouth of [[Kara River]], north-east of the [[Pay-Khoy Ridge]] (a continuation of the northern [[Ural Mountains]]). It is of diameter 50–60&nbsp;km and filled with [[Quaternary]] [[deposit (geology)|deposit]]s.<ref name=igr>[http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00206817609471165#.U95qLvldWSo Structure of the Kara depression], International Geology Review Volume 18, Issue 1, 1976, {{doi|10.1080/00206817609471165}} (a translation of the article "О строении Карской депрессии", ''Sovetskaya Geologiya'', 1976, no. 3)</ref>

The depression is part of the [[Pechora coal basin]].

