{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Nelson Falls | photo = Nelson Falls.jpg | photo_width = 280px | photo_caption = Nelson Falls | map = Tasmania | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|42|05|24|S|145|43|48|E|region:AU-TAS_type:waterbody_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=ga1>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Nelson Falls (TAS)|feature=TAS23447}}</ref> | location = [[Western Tasmania|West Coast]], [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]] | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Cascade]] | elevation = | height = {{convert|30|m}}<ref name=wow>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-nelson-falls.html|title=Nelson Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|publisher=Johnny T. Cheng|date=29 November 2006|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref> | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Nelson Falls''', a [[Waterfall#Types|cascade waterfall]], is located in the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage Area|World Heritage]]{{endash}}listed [[Tasmanian Wilderness]], in the [[Western Tasmania|West Coast]] region of [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]].
==Location and features== The Nelson Falls are situated in the [[Franklin-Gordon Wild Rivers National Park]], accessible from {{TAScity|Queenstown}}, located {{convert|27|km}} to the west, via the [[Lyell Highway]] through the Nelson Valley. The falls descend approximately {{convert|30|m}}.<ref name=wow/>
