'''Tuscia''' is a historical region of [[Italy]] that comprised the territories under [[Etruscan civilization|Etruscan]] influence and the name adopted for [[Etruria]] after the Roman conquest. While it later came to coincide with today’s [[province of Viterbo]], it was originally much larger, including the whole region of [[Tuscany]], a great part of [[Umbria]] and the northern parts of [[Lazio]].
==Villages== *[[Castel Cellesi]] *[[Vejano]]
